# Contributing to BlockRS

Thank you for your interest in contributing to BlockRS! This document provides guidelines and instructions for contributing.

## Code of Conduct

By participating in this project, you agree to abide by our [Code of Conduct](CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md).

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites
- Git
- BDWGC
- secp256k1

### Setting Up Development Environment
1. Fork the repository
2. Clone your fork:
    ```
    git clone --recurse-submodules https://github.com/shrehanrajsingh/blockrs.git
    ```
3. Add the upstream repository:
    ```
    git remote add upstream https://github.com/shrehanrajsingh/blockrs.git
    ```
4. Install dependencies [if applicable]

## How to Contribute

### Reporting Bugs
- Use the issue tracker
- Describe the bug clearly
- Include steps to reproduce
- Specify your environment details

### Suggesting Features
- Use the issue tracker
- Clearly describe the feature
- Explain why it would be valuable

### Pull Requests
1. Create a branch for your work
2. Make your changes
3. Test your changes
4. Submit a pull request
5. Update your PR based on feedback

## Style Guidelines
- Use clang-format in accordance with `.clang-format/` to properly format your code

## Commit Guidelines
- Use clear commit messages
- Reference issue numbers when applicable

## License
By contributing, you agree that your contributions will be licensed under the project's license.